name: tree seedling production, in unheated greenhouse | tree seedling, for planting | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/10669/documentation

The dataset refers to the production of 1000 tree seedlings. The dataset contains the production of tree seedlings in a tree nursery  for plantation in forests. The seedlings are produced in an unheated greenhouse and packed for transport.;The seedlings go with a packaging of 1.05 kg of growing dras (HDPE), 3.65 kg of plant boxes from cardboard and 0.0525 kg of strech wrap (LLDPE), to be recycled or disposed of after planting

The activity starts with the establishment of the greenhouse with HDPE film and considers soil improvement, fertilization, transport of inputs and transport packaging materials.The dataset also contains the disposal of the transport packaging (after plantation of the seedling).

The activity ends with the seedlings packed for transportation. The dataset does not contain data on water use, frame infrastructure of the greenhouse and on the use of fungicides, insecticides etc. as source does not provide this information.

exchanges.description: Total amount of active substance/s of fertilisers needed for the production of 'tree seedling, for planting' is calculated to be circa 6.09E-04 kg. Fertiliser/s used in this dataset is/are: 'nitrogen fertiliser, as N'. The total amount of active substance/s is doubled in order to account for the packaging of the dilluted product of fertiliser/s that is/are applied. Therefore, 1.22E-03 kg of packaging for fertilisers is justified with this exchange.
